description:
In today's Daily Fix:
The new Battle Pass for Fortnite: Chapter 5 - Season 3 is now live and it comes with a new biome, new outfits, new...well, a lot of things. Most importantly, the iconic T-60 Power Armor from the Fallout franchise will be available (after some grinding), allowing you to conquer the new Wasteland biome in style. Also available in the Battle Pass is an outfit that turns you into everyone's favorite magnetically charged mutant, Magneto. In other news, Naughty Dog's Neil Druckmann shared his thoughts on AI in an interview with Sony. Druckmann seems pretty optimistic about how new AI tools can enhance storytelling in games, but did bring up concerns over the ethics of such tools. And finally, hot on the heels of The Joker in The Suicide Squad: Kill the Justice League comes a new villain.

#IGN #Gaming #Fortnite
title: Fortnite Chapter 5 Season 3 Adds Fallout, Magneto Outfit - IGN Daily Fix

description:
Atlas reviewed by Matt Donato. Now streaming on Netflix.
Atlas earns more than a shrug, even if it won’t settle relevant and alarming debates about artificial intelligence’s place in contemporary society. Brad Peyton oversees a futuristic action thriller that frequently plays like a clone of other cautionary tales about AI – but those movies, shows, games, and books don’t have Peyton’s secret weapon: Jennifer Lopez. She’s able to command the screen, bicker with software programs, and sell a convincing heroine’s arc from behind a mech-suit’s windshield. Atlas is far from the “Justice for AI!” disaster its premise implies, and while it’s not the next groundbreaking sci-fi epic, it earns points for building an entertaining, adequately executed movie around a hot-button topic.
title: Atlas Review

description:
In today's Fix of entertainment news:
HBO's The Last of Us Season 2 has found an actor for Isaac, and it's a familiar face to the franchise. Oscar-nominated actor Jeffrey Wright will return to the role he originated in the video game, The Last of Us Part 2. Isaac is the leader of the Washington Liberation Front, a militant group that rules over Seattle. He's not the first actor to return to the franchise's live-action form, as Merle Dandridge portrayed Marlene both in the game and Season 1 of the HBO show. In other news, Ryan Reynolds has revealed new casting for Deadpool & Wolverine: Rob McElhenny. That's right, Mac from It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia, and Co-owner of Wrexham AFC (along with Reynolds) is joining the movie in an undisclosed role. And finally, Rian Johnson's next Knives Out movie has a title: Wake Up Dead Man. Daniel Craig is expected to return as sleuth Benoit Blanc.

#IGN
title: Jeffrey Wright (Re)Joins the Cast of The Last of Us Season 2 - IGN The Fix: Entertainment

description: Louise (Karen Gillan), a 28-year-old Brooklynite adrift in life, finds herself suddenly single and grappling with her identity as a musician. While she struggles with her underlying depression, a reckless drunken stumble lands her with a broken hip, and leads to a stint in a physical therapy ward with patients twice her age. Here, she crosses paths with Antonina (Margaret Sophie Stein), a cantankerous elderly Polish woman who speaks no English. Reluctantly, Louise takes on the role of Antonina's caregiver, a situation neither of them welcomes. As they navigate their begrudging relationship, they confront the realities of aging, forcing Louise to consider her own journey into adulthood.
title: Late Bloomers - Official Trailer (2024) Karen Gillan, Margaret Sophie Stein

description:
Here's the Descendants: The Rise of Red trailer for the next installment in Descendants franchise. The music-driven Disney original movie will be available to stream exclusively on Disney+ from July 12, 2024, followed by a special encore on August 9 on Disney Channel.

Former Villain Kid Uma, now Auradon Prep’s newest principal, extends an invite to the school to another VK – Red, the rebellious daughter of the Queen of Hearts from Wonderland. After the Queen of Hearts incites a coup against Auradon, Red and Cinderella’s daughter Chloe travel back in time to try to undo the traumatic event that set Red’s mother down her villainous path. 

Descendants: The Rise of Red stars Brandy, Rita Ora, Kylie Cantrall, Malia Baker, China Anne McClain, Jeremy Swift, Dara Reneé, Ruby Rose Turner, Morgan Dudley, Paolo Montalban, Melanie Paxson, Leonardo Nam, Joshua Colley, and Peder Lindell.

The film is written by Dan Frey and Russell Sommer, and directed by Jennifer Phang. Suzanne Todd and Gary Mar
title: Descendants: The Rise of Red - Official Trailer (2024) Rita Ora, Kylie Cantrall

description:
In this exclusive clip from the documentary Frank Miller: American Genius, Miller explains why he left Marvel Comics for DC in order to create his "masterless samurai" comic book Ronin.

Frank Miller: American Genius explores the near half-century career of Frank Miller, the legendary comic book artist and writer, and features interviews and cameos from his admirers, students, and collaborators, including Neal Adams, Robert Rodriguez, Jessica Alba, Jim Lee, Zack Snyder, Stan Lee, and more. The film was produced, written and directed by Silenn Thomas for Frank Miller Ink.  
 
Set to screen simultaneously in Cinemark theaters nationwide on Monday, June 10, the event will feature a live introduction with Frank Miller moderated by Rosario Dawson, and all ticket holders will receive an exclusive custom collectible.

For tickets and more information, visit  https://www.cinemark.com/movies/frank-miller-american-genius-with-live-intro-and-exclusive-custom-collectible
title: Frank Miller: American Genius - Exclusive Clip (2024)
